  "notes": "Data is for the classic Llebeig+Gregal 18 (RFEG recorrido 'CAMPO LA SELLA - Llebeig+Gregal'), the combination the RFEG lists first. Per-hole pars and meters for Blancas/Amarillas/Rojas match mScorecard exactly (totals 6232/5964/5227). Naranjas (orange) tees have no allowed color match, mapped to gray. RFEG also rates two other combinations, all par 72: Llebeig+Mestral (Blancas 6225m, M 74.0/137, F 80.8/145; Amarillas 5798m, M 71.8/133, F 78.0/139; Rojas 5152m, M 68.8/122, F 73.9/135; Naranjas 4617m, M 65.8/113, F 70.7/125; Mestral back-nine pars 3-5-4-4-5-3-4-5-3, SI 4,8,16,2,14,18,10,6,12) and Gregal+Mestral (Blancas 6123m, M 73.2/133, F 79.8/147; Amarillas 5730m, M 71.1/129, F 77.3/144; Rojas 5077m, M 68.0/124, F 73.2/132; Naranjas 4560m, M 65.0/114, F 69.9/123; Gregal-as-front SI 7,1,15,13,11,17,3,5,9). A special 'R&A Student Tour Series' rating also exists (Blancas M 6188m 74.0/137; Rojas F 5378m 75.9/137) using mixed tee positions. Minor discrepancy: golfify.io shows Gregal front-nine SI as even numbers (8,2,16...) for the Gregal+Mestral combo, whereas RFEG's official allocation gives Gregal odd SI (7,1,15...) when it is the front nine; RFEG taken as authoritative. Stroke index shown is identical for all tees/genders on the RFEG card."
